// ===========================================================================
//  Cyclo web — the FX-view framework (the effect minigames, on web).
//
//  This is the web port of the native per-effect editors (src/app/ReverbView.h,
//  DelayView.h, DriveView.h, CrushView.h, FilterView.h, …) and the FX rack flow
//  (FxRackView.h + MainComponent::applyEffectClause). It is DATA-DRIVEN: every
//  effect is one entry in FX_DESCRIPTORS (params, ranges, labels, signature colour
//  + a small canvas "world" motif). Adding the remaining ~9 effects is filling a
//  descriptor — no new plumbing.
//
//  The round-trip (the "coin"): tapping an effect call in the CODE editor — e.g.
//  `.reverb(0.35)` — parses THAT call's args, opens a touch editor bound to them,
//  and every drag REWRITES only that call's argument list in the document text
//  (everything else byte-preserved), which the engine hot-swaps live so the change
//  is HEARD immediately. Exactly the native gesture->coin->re-eval loop, faithful to
//  MainComponent::applyEffectClause / applyFilterClause (balanced-paren splice).
//
//  The PURE half (findEffectCall / parseArgs / buildClause / rewriteCall / the
//  descriptors) imports nothing DOM-y and runs in Node too, so web/verify.js can assert
//  the doc round-trip headlessly. The DOM half (createFxEditor) is browser-only and
//  is only ever called from the browser bundle.
//
//  INPUT-AGNOSTIC (memory cyclo-web-input-agnostic, docs/web-interaction.md): the drag-rows
//  reuse the shared attachValueDrag gesture — one Pointer-Events path (mouse/touch/pen +
//  capture), an occlusion-safe floating readout bubble ABOVE the finger, mouse-wheel + arrow-key
//  fine-tune, and the "pull away = finer resolution" touch trick. No per-effect input plumbing.
// ===========================================================================
import { attachValueDrag } from './gesture.js';   // top-level pure in Node (DOM touched only when called)
import { registerOverlay } from './overlay.js';   // the ONE shared open/close/scrim/Escape manager

